Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon. milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until well blended. Gently stir in half of the whipped topping. Spread into crust. Pour 1 cup milk into large bowl. Add pumpkin, pudding mixes cinnamon, ginger, and cloves. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. (Mixture will be thick.) Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish with remaining whipped topping. Store leftover pie in refrigerator.